                                    "abstract": "Wang Yi, a member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China and Foreign Minister, met with Indian Foreign Minister Subrahmanyam Jaishankar in Rio de Janeiro. Wang Yi stated that the meeting between Chinese President Xi Jinping and Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi in Kazan has successfully restarted the Sino-Indian relationship. Both sides should respect each other's core interests, enhance mutual trust through dialogue and communication, and handle differences with sincerity and integrity to push the two countries' relations back to a stable and healthy development track as soon as possible. He emphasized the need to send more positive signals, do more things that benefit the two countries' interactions, increase mutual trust, reduce suspicion, and promote cooperation. Efforts should be made to achieve practical progress in areas such as resuming direct flights, mutual dispatch of journalists, and visa facilitation as soon as possible. Wang Yi pointed out that as two neighboring major developing countries, the common interests of China and India far outweigh their differences, and both sides should view each other's development as an opportunity. Both China and India adhere to a non-aligned foreign policy, uphold multilateralism, and support the democratization of international relations. They should continue to strengthen coordination and cooperation in international affairs, promoting greater development of the BRICS mechanism and the Shanghai Cooperation Organization. Subrahmanyam Jaishankar expressed that India hopes to restart the dialogue mechanism as soon as possible. The consensus between India and China is much greater than their differences, and both sides should view bilateral relations with a strategic perspective and handle relevant issues with a more positive attitude, not allowing specific differences to define the relationship between the two countries.",
                                    "content": "中共中央政治局委員、外長王毅在里約熱內盧,會見印度外長蘇傑生。 王毅表示,國家主席習近平和總理莫迪在喀山成功會見,中印關係重啟再出發。雙方要尊重彼此核心利益,通過對話溝通增進互信,秉持誠意誠信妥處分歧,推動兩國關係早日重回穩定健康發展軌道。 他說,要多發出積極信號,多做有利於兩國交往的事情;多增進互信,少一些猜忌;多開展合作,少一些消耗。爭取儘快在恢復直航、互派記者、便利簽證等方面取得實際進展。 王毅指出,作為相鄰的兩個發展中大國,中印共同利益遠遠大於分歧,雙方應把彼此發展視為機遇。中印都奉行不結盟的外交政策,都堅持多邊主義,支持國際關係民主化,要繼續在國際事務中加強協調配合,推動金磚機制、上海合作組織取得更大發展。 蘇傑生表示,印方希望儘快重啟對話機制。印中之間共識遠大於分歧,雙方應以戰略眼光看待雙邊關係,以更積極態度妥善處理有關問題,不讓具體分歧定義兩國關係。",
