                                    "news_id": 267307388,
                                    "data_source": "world_news_api",
                                    "abstract": "TEHRAN, Nov. 25 (MNA) – Iran’s Special Representative for Afghanistan Affairs Hassan Kazemi Qomi met and held talks with Chinese counterpart Yue Xiaoyong on Monday to discuss relevant issues.",
                                    "content": "During the talks, the two sides emphasized the need for countering terrorism, need to strengthen the initiative of the Regional Contact Group with the aim of establishing peace and stability and preventing the divisive foreign interventions in Afghanistan.\n\nBack on September 9, Qomi, who was Iranian president's special envoy for Afghanistan said that Islamic Republic of Iran is resolved to complete the border wall with the neighboring countries of Afghanistan and Pakistan.",
