                                    "abstract": "Speaker of the National Assembly of Pakistan, Ayaz Sadiq, expressed his desire to enhance economic and trade ties with Russia during a meeting with the Speaker of the Federation Council of the Russian Federation, Valentina Matvienko. The meeting took place in Moscow, where Sadiq led a parliamentary delegation. He highlighted the importance of strengthening parliamentary cooperation to solidify ties between the two countries. Sadiq also mentioned recent high-level engagements, including meetings between the Presidents and Prime Ministers of both nations, and visits by Russian and Pakistani officials, as encouraging developments. He emphasized the need to enhance interactions between the parliamentarians of both nations and reiterated Pakistan's desire to strengthen economic and trade ties with Russia. Matvienko expressed Russia's high regard for its growing diplomatic, parliamentary, and economic relations with Pakistan and stated that the meeting marks a significant step toward fortifying bilateral relations and exploring new avenues of collaboration between the two countries.",
                                    "content": "ISLAMABAD, (UrduPoint / Pakistan Point News - 29th Nov, 2024) Speaker has said that wanted to enhance its economic and trade ties with Federation. The Speaker along with a parliamentary delegation called on the Speaker of the Council of the Federal of the Federation, Ms. Valentina Matvienko, at the Federal of , said a press release received here on Friday The parliamentary delegation comprised Members of the Rana Muhammad Hayat Khan, Syed Agha Rafiullah, Abdul Qadir Patel, Dr. Muhammad , and Sher Ali Arbab. During his meeting, Ayaz Sadiq has expressed gratitude for the warm reception extended by Ms. Valentina Matvienko to him and his delegation. Ms. Valentina Matvienko, referencing her recent to , lauded the hospitality and reception extended to her by ’s . Ayaz Sadiq while underscoring the significance of strengthening Pak-Russia parliamentary ties said that parliamentary cooperation could play a pivotal role in solidifying ties between both the countries. He appreciated the participation and support of his counterpart at the first Speakers’ Conference held at under the auspices of the of in 2014. Ayaz Sadiq also said that the invitation extended to him by his counterpart to officially is an important step towards strengthening parliamentary ties. The Speaker expressed satisfaction with the growing ties between the two countries at the parliamentary, diplomatic, and governmental levels. He highlighted recent high-level engagements, including meetings between the Presidents and Prime Ministers of both nations, the of 's Deputy to , Ms. Matvienko's to , and visits by 's Federal Ministers for Energy and Privatization to , as encouraging developments. Ayaz Sadiq emphasized the need to enhance interactions between the parliamentarians of both nations. He reiterated 's desire to strengthen economic and trade ties between and . He further stressed the importance of fostering connections between the communities of both countries to promote economic and trade cooperation. Ms. Valentina Matvienko said that highly values its growing diplomatic, parliamentary, and economic relations with . She further said that this meeting marks a significant step toward fortifying bilateral relations and exploring new avenues of collaboration between and .",
