                                    "content": "International\n\nExclusive Videos\n\nBudget 2024-25\n\nBudget 2023-24\n\nFederal Budget 2023-24\n\nPunjab Budget 23-24\n\nSindh Budget 23-24\n\nKPK Budget 23-24\n\nBalochistan Budget 23-24\n\nBudget 2022-23\n\nBudget 2021-22\n\nBudget 2020-21\n\nBudget 2019-20\n\nBudget 2018-19\n\nBudget 2016-17\n\nIndependence Day\n\nDefence Day\n\nKashmir Black Day\n\n12 Rabi ul Awal\n\nGeneral Coverage\n\nPhoto Feature\n\nPolitical Activity\n\nEntertainment\n\nTuesday, November 19, 2024\n\nWelcome! Log into your account\n\nyour username\n\nyour password\n\nForgot your password? Get help\n\nPassword recovery\n\nRecover your password\n\nA password will be e-mailed to you.\n\nAssociated Press Of Pakistan\n\nInternational\n\nExclusive Videos\n\nBudget 2024-25\n\nBudget 2023-24\n\nFederal Budget 2023-24\n\nPunjab Budget 23-24\n\nSindh Budget 23-24\n\nKPK Budget 23-24\n\nBalochistan Budget 23-24\n\nBudget 2022-23\n\nBudget 2021-22\n\nBudget 2020-21\n\nBudget 2019-20\n\nBudget 2018-19\n\nBudget 2016-17\n\nIndependence Day\n\nDefence Day\n\nKashmir Black Day\n\n12 Rabi ul Awal\n\nGeneral Coverage\n\nPhoto Feature\n\nPolitical Activity\n\nEntertainment\n\nHomeNationalPak, Kazakh sides hold BPC; review bilateral cooperation \n\nPak, Kazakh sides hold BPC; review bilateral cooperation \n\n- Advertisement -\n\nISLAMABAD, Nov19 (APP): Pakistan and Kazakhstan Tuesday held the third round of Bilateral Political Consultations (BPC) in which the two sides comprehensively reviewed the bilateral cooperation. \n\nAdditional Foreign Secretary (Afghanistan & West Asia) Ambassador Ahmad Naseem Warraich led the Pakistan side while the Kazakh side was led by Deputy Minister for Foreign Affairs, Ambassador Alibek Bakayev. \n\n“The two sides comprehensively reviewed the bilateral cooperation between Pakistan and Kazakhstan, including political relations, inter-parliamentary exchanges, economic & trade ties, connectivity, education, information technology, telecommunication, culture and tourism,” Foreign Office Spokesperson said in a press release. \n- Advertisement -\n\nExpressing satisfaction at the current trajectory of bilateral relations, the two sides reaffirmed their commitment to maintaining the momentum in bilateral cooperation, and to collaborate closely at multilateral fora. \n\nIt was agreed to enhance bilateral trade and economic relations and to expand collaboration in tourism and information technology. \n\nImportant regional and global developments, including the situation in Ukraine, Afghanistan and Indian Illegally Occupied Jammu & Kashmir were also discussed. \n\n- Advertisement -\n\nRELATED ARTICLES\n\nCDA chief inspects construction work on Sarena Chowk, F8 Interchanges\n\nTue, 19 Nov 2024, 9:39 PM\n\nDPM/FM Dar, Netherlands FM discuss bilateral ties \n\nTue, 19 Nov 2024, 9:36 PM\n\nThose who obstructs Pakistan’s security to face consequence: COAS\n\nTue, 19 Nov 2024, 9:28 PM\n\nMost Popular\n\nIntensity of smog decreases in Punjab; Lahore still polluted\n\nTue, 19 Nov 2024, 9:49 PM\n\nCostumers purchasing figs from vendor at Joint Road as the demand increased due to chilled weather engulfs the city.\n\nTue, 19 Nov 2024, 9:47 PM\n\nLESCO resolves 1,136 complaints last day\n\nTue, 19 Nov 2024, 9:47 PM\n\nGood news is coming in the economic field:Rana Mashhood\n\nTue, 19 Nov 2024, 9:47 PM\n\nAPPASSOCIATED PRESS OF PAKISTAN \n\nServing the nation since 1947 by providing an accurate, objective, uninterrupted flow of news to the people, the national news service is pursuing a comprehensive strategy to transform the existing news operations into a forward-looking service – APP Digital for its diverse subscriber-base and the public.\n\nContact us: news@app.com.pk\n\nCopyright © Associated Press of Pakistan \n\nTender Notice\n\nPublic Service Message\n\nFinal Seniority List\n\nMemorandums",
